01/06/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- A joint operation by Turkish and Italian border police Friday (30 May) resulted in the seizure of 189.5kg of heroin and the detainment of nine people. 
The operation was launched after Turkish border police received a tip that a large amount of heroin was to be smuggled out of Turkey. 
Local police confiscated 59.8kg of heroin in two trucks and 38.1kg of heroin in a minivan in Istanbul, while Italian border police found 91.5kg of heroin hidden in two trucks at the Italian port of Trieste. 
Police say the heroin seized in Turkey was headed towards Germany and the Netherlands, while the stashes found in Italy came from Turkey and was of Afghan origin. 
(Anadolu Agency, AFP - 30/05/03)
